   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Advancing UNIDO best practice on compliance and partner outreach</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In the light of increasing demand for PCD services and the limited available resources, the objective of the project is to maintain and enhance UNIDO#s efforts in the field of compliance and partner outreach to assure best practice throughout operations and accelerate implementation of ISID.  In the area of compliance this project assures: (i) compliance with regards to environmental and social safeguards (ESS) for the entire UNIDO portfolio; (ii) compliance with Environmental, Social and Governance (ESG) standards of all prospective business sector pa rtnerships; as well as (iii) compliance with fiduciary and ESS environmental and social safeguards standards of prospective financial institutions (FI) partners.  In the area of partner outreach the project promotes: (i) engagement of UNIDO#s partners in the Organization#s work (including due diligence checks, partnership monitoring and risk mitigation/monitoring), as a means to reach increased impact in the context of Programmes for Country Partnership (PCP), Country Partnership (CP), bilateral programmes and post COVID-19 industrial and socioeconomic recovery programmes; as well as (ii) UNIDO#s organization of and participation in major partnership events (e.g.  FI annual meetings, UN Global Compact (UNGC) meetings, etc.), webinars, and missions (after lifting</narrative>
  </description>
